[[!meta title="Sound and video"]]

Tails includes several sound and video applications:

  - **<span class="application">[Audacity](http://audacity.sourceforge.net/)</span>** is a multi-track audio editor
    designed for recording, playing and editing of digital audio.
    See the [official documentation](http://manual.audacityteam.org/o/).

  - **<span class="application">[Brasero](http://projects.gnome.org/brasero/)</span>** is an application to burn,
    copy, and erase CD and DVD media: audio, video, or data.
    See the [official documentation](https://help.gnome.org/users/brasero/stable/).

  - **<span class="application">[Pitivi](http://www.pitivi.org/)</span>** is a video editor.
    See the [official documentation](http://www.pitivi.org/manual/).

  - **<span class="application">[Sound Juicer](http://burtonini.com/blog/computers/sound-juicer)</span>** is a CD
    ripper application.

  - **<span class="application">[Traverso](http://traverso-daw.org/)</span>** is a multi-track audio recorder and
    editor.

These applications can be started from the
